				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="M. Gourmand" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Collect ingredients from the board game until you have gathered all items indicated on your dessert card. But watch out! Mr. Gourmand will try to eat your ingredients and your opponents might rummage through your stash of food!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal of the game : Complete two dessert recipes. &amp;#10; To complete a recipe, you must collect the three basic ingredients indicated on your card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play? Draw a card and move your pawn on the board the number of spaces indicated on the card to collect the ingredient associated with the square where you end your move. You can also choose to move your pawn and take a slimy fly waffles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you draw a Mr. Gourmand card, all players (including you) must feed Mr. Gourmand by putting one of their own ingredient on his stomach.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The third time Mr. Gourmand is drawn, he has eaten too&amp;#10;much and his belly explodes! The player who drew&amp;#10;Mr. Gourmand chooses an ingredient from&amp;#10;Mr. Gourmand&amp;rsquo;s belly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have a slimy fly waffles, you can steal an opponent&amp;rsquo;s&amp;#10;ingredient. You can also use them to feed Mr. Gourmand to get a protection card (that will protect you from next Mr. Gourmand visit).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This board game asks children to think about what they need and how to get it. With the different elements of surprise, the game makes them laugh too! M. Gourmand is quick to install and play. And it's fun to play for all ages!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a bonus, the 15 recipes of the game are available on the Internet to make them in real life. Ideal for prolonging family fun and feasting!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
